      "id": "commentary",
      "html": "<h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Curbera convincingly suggests that the second character on line 4 is the Greek symbol for one half, found in papyri and inscriptions, giving an age of 2.5, rather than an inverted numeral 32 or 12 with a Latin L or a Greek iota.</p>  "
